reviewText: We all loved it. Had to cover very young daughters eyes more for teen kiss scenes as she was paying ardent attention and beginning to talk about them "falling in love". She's 4 so we're not ready for those thoughts yet! There were more teen romance scenes than in Flicka "Country Pride", but overall still a very clean family movie. Enjoyed and would rent again.
summary: Great Flicka movie, perhaps a little too much teen romance for the very young ones.

reviewText: Happy, horse movie with nice scenary for the pre-teen daughters who like to ride. Both were crying, with the wife at the sad parts. Dad was pleased that they were happy. Good news is there are several of these movies with a more or less repeatable theme: wild daughter, wild horse, come together, moment of truth for horse and daughter, sad interlude, followed by happiness and fairytale ending....sure beats the evening news.
summary: If your daughter likes horses, this will be a winner

reviewText: sequels  are rarely as good as the original. Flicka 2 falls into that category too. However instead of trying to continue on the story from where Flicka left off, Flicka 2 is a new story, although basically the same idea. There are all new characters, all new issues all new solutions.a horrid neighbor ends up getting Flicka. Carrie has to get her back, during this story, Carrie learns to go from city girl to sorta country girl. She learns to ride, learns to love the horses. Flicka in particular. She over comes problems her way and adapts to life on the ranch.She and her Dad learn to be a family., save Flicka and have a happy ending for all.Flicka 2 did not make me cry like Flicka did. But I still think this movie is one worth buying. If you like family friendly horse movies that is.
Title: Flicka 2

reviewText: We rented Flicka 2 and watched it.  I suppose people with a lot of horse knowledge could pick it a part but we enjoyed it.  It was a good story about a teenage girl restoring her relationship with her Dad. I enjoyed seeing Patrick Warburton play a sympathetic character instead of his typical "dufas" kind of role.  The leading lady was likable and the story spent a little time, at the beginning, creating awareness of the Wild Mustang roundups that are going on in our nation. Our family enjoyed it.
Title: Flicka 2

reviewText: So much better then the Flicka movie.  Interesting story line and characters.  A great afternoon movie to watch with your kids.
